## 4. Clone and Prepare Your GitHub Repository

### 4.1 Set Up SSH for GitHub (Recommended)
```bash
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "you@email.com"
cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub
```
Add the key to GitHub → Settings → SSH Keys

### 4.2 Clone the Repository
```bash
ssh -T git@github.com // test git SSH connection

mkdir -p ~/sites
cd ~/sites
git clone git@github.com:USERNAME/REPO.git // for SSH clone
git remote set-url origin git@github.com:username/repository.git // for HTTPS connection
git remote -v // verify connection
cd REPO
```

### 4.3 Verify Project Structure
Typical structure:
```
index.html
/css
/js
/assets
```
Ensure `index.html` is at the root or adjust server config accordingly.
